	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Anyone Else reproduced Fire Emblem and Famicom Wars?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">FARID wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What about the other pins of the MMC4?</div><br />MMC2 has these pins that the MMC4 doesn't: PPU A0, A1, A2. (Not known why it was ever included, it's not useful); CHR A16 (twice as much CHR)<br />MMC4 has these pins that the MMC2 doesn't: PRG A17 (twice as much PRG); PRG RAM +CE and /CE (support WRAM)<br /><br />Since the MMC4 seems to not provide a toggleable PRG RAM protection bit, using a 74'20, 74'138, or 74'139 for equivalent ends would be fine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


